  "notes": [
    "PREPARATION FOR THE MINOR CSE 12: Computer Systems and Assembly Language and Lab CSE 16: Applied Discrete Mathematics CSE 20: Beginning Programming in Python CSE 30: Programming Abstractions: Python CSE 13S: Computer Systems and C Programming OR ECE 13: Computer Systems and C Programming AM 10: Mathematical Methods for Engineers I OR MATH 21: Linear Algebra One of the following calculus series: MATH 11A: Calculus with Applications AND MATH 11B: Calculus with Applications OR MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics AND MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics Please visit the Baskin Engineering Undergraduate Experience website to learn more about this minor.",
    "UC Santa Cruz students may choose to complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and allowable credits. While a minor will appear on a student's official transcript, it will not be listed on their diploma. Pursuing a minor is a personal decision that should align with a student's educational and career goals. Students do not apply for minors when submitting their application to UC Santa Cruz. After enrolling, transfer students interested in pursuing a minor should contact the department offering the minor for guidance."
